WEBVTT

00:01.251 --> 00:02.752
Previously on
"Our Kind of People"...

00:02.752 --> 00:04.354
Is there something going on
with you and Lauren?

00:04.421 --> 00:05.122
Jack Harmon.

00:05.489 --> 00:07.857
He had some important papers
that I urgently need.

00:07.857 --> 00:09.193
Raymond: Mind if I take a look
at those documents

00:09.193 --> 00:10.860
before you take them back
to Franklin Holdings?

00:10.860 --> 00:13.297
Darius' death
is on my hands.

00:13.297 --> 00:15.199
I'm going to
turn myself in.

00:15.199 --> 00:18.034
Angela no longer
has a place in this family.

00:18.034 --> 00:20.204
Olivia: I'm sorry, Ms. Vaughn.
You did not make the cut.

00:20.204 --> 00:22.339
Getting this deal memo
means a lot to me.

00:22.339 --> 00:24.808
You'd make a good inside man
if you stayed on.
I'm in.

00:24.808 --> 00:27.311
Piggy knew you would try to talk
her out of turning herself in.

00:27.311 --> 00:28.678
Left you and Nik these.

00:28.678 --> 00:31.148
Piggy: There is nothing
that will stop me.

00:31.948 --> 00:33.550
[ Door opens ]

00:39.889 --> 00:41.057
Angela?

00:46.563 --> 00:48.298
What's wrong?

00:48.298 --> 00:49.699
It's Piggy.

00:49.699 --> 00:51.501
She went down
to the police station

00:51.501 --> 00:53.337
and turned herself in

00:53.337 --> 00:55.839
for murdering
Darius Bates.

00:55.839 --> 00:57.574
You helped her
cover it up.

00:57.574 --> 00:59.476
You know
it was self-defense.

00:59.476 --> 01:01.745
Can you please help her?

01:01.745 --> 01:05.048
I mean, you got Nate out
of prison with a phone call.

01:05.048 --> 01:06.516
Please.

01:06.516 --> 01:08.485
I'll d-do whatever.

01:08.485 --> 01:09.719
Hmm.

01:11.421 --> 01:14.758
Both you and I are stubborn,
bull-headed,

01:14.758 --> 01:17.494
and laser-focused
on what we want for our family.

01:17.494 --> 01:19.763
So I will help Piggy.

01:19.763 --> 01:22.666
Additionally, I will set up
a generous trust for Nikki

01:22.666 --> 01:25.935
and ample seed money
for Eve's Crown,

01:25.935 --> 01:29.206
enough for you to handle
your own distribution.

01:29.206 --> 01:32.209
Well, what do you want
in return?

01:33.277 --> 01:36.180
Leave Oak Bluffs

01:36.180 --> 01:37.881
for good.

01:37.881 --> 01:40.784
Angela, as much as
I've come to love you and Nikki,

01:40.784 --> 01:42.085
there are just things

01:42.085 --> 01:44.788
that are more difficult
with you here,

01:44.788 --> 01:47.357
things I can't have you
digging up.

01:47.357 --> 01:48.592
"Things."
Mm-hmm.

01:48.592 --> 01:51.228
I was right.
You're hiding something.

01:58.235 --> 02:00.870
At least you finally said it
to my face.

02:04.641 --> 02:05.942
Couple of weeks ago,

02:05.942 --> 02:07.411
I thought that
having you in my life

02:07.411 --> 02:09.213
would make me feel whole.

02:09.213 --> 02:11.548
I'm already whole.

02:11.548 --> 02:13.149
And Piggy is
a part of that.

02:13.149 --> 02:15.919
So, I'll consider your offer
to help her.

02:18.322 --> 02:20.590
But my God.

02:20.590 --> 02:22.992
What a disappointment
you are.

02:22.992 --> 02:25.829
**

02:25.829 --> 02:28.565
[ Door opens, closes ]

02:28.565 --> 02:30.300
**

02:30.300 --> 02:31.835
* Head high

02:31.835 --> 02:33.570
* Confident

02:33.570 --> 02:35.305
* Strong mind

02:35.305 --> 02:36.840
* Resilient

02:36.840 --> 02:41.578
* You can't break me,
I was born to rise *

02:41.578 --> 02:44.648
* Our kind of people

02:44.648 --> 02:48.017
* Ooh, ooh

02:48.017 --> 02:51.187
* Our kind of people

02:51.187 --> 02:55.091
* Ooh, ooh

02:59.195 --> 03:04.334
**

03:04.334 --> 03:06.836
* You got me right
where you want me *

03:06.836 --> 03:08.772
* If you never leave me lonely

03:08.772 --> 03:11.140
* I can the one, be the only

03:11.140 --> 03:13.277
* Long as you keep
showing me love *

03:13.277 --> 03:15.645
* Got me right
where you want me *

03:15.645 --> 03:17.681
* Say you never
leave me lonely *

03:17.681 --> 03:19.849
* I can the one, be the only

03:19.849 --> 03:21.217
* I could be the best thing

03:21.217 --> 03:24.888
* For you, you, you, you,
you, you, you *

03:24.888 --> 03:26.856
* I could be the best, be the,
be the best thing for you *
Okay.

03:26.856 --> 03:29.559
Okay.
Where's the party?

03:29.559 --> 03:31.561
Right here!
Look.

03:31.561 --> 03:32.896
Beads or no beads?
Beads.

03:32.896 --> 03:35.532
Gee, it's like --
it's like 3:00 a.m.,

03:35.532 --> 03:37.401
and it's --
Oh.

03:37.401 --> 03:39.636
3:07.

03:39.636 --> 03:40.904
What up?

03:40.904 --> 03:42.171
Couldn't sleep.

03:42.171 --> 03:46.209
Some people count sheep.
I count braids.

03:49.145 --> 03:50.847
You want to talk about it?
Talk about what?

03:50.847 --> 03:52.649
How I went to see
Teddy today,

03:52.649 --> 03:53.917
asking for help
with Piggy,

03:53.917 --> 03:57.921
and he told me,
yeah, he'll help,

03:57.921 --> 04:00.757
as long as I leave the island
for good?

04:00.757 --> 04:02.191
Why would
he want that?

04:02.191 --> 04:04.694
Good question.

04:04.694 --> 04:06.195
'Cause he's shook.

04:06.195 --> 04:08.732
'Cause I'm getting closer
to the truth.

04:08.732 --> 04:09.933
[ Scoffs ]

04:09.933 --> 04:12.068
Look, I know Teddy
framed my mother

04:12.068 --> 04:14.604
for drug possession
in the '80s.

04:14.604 --> 04:18.074
He wanted her gone then
just like he wants me gone now.

04:18.074 --> 04:20.510
That's why he made Leah
shut me out the Graceties.

04:20.510 --> 04:21.845
They think they're gonna

04:21.845 --> 04:23.413
just close off
their little social clubs,

04:23.413 --> 04:26.416
and I'm gonna just give up
and dip? [ Scoffs ]

04:26.416 --> 04:29.185
Gee, maybe you should take
this deal.
Nate, please.

04:29.185 --> 04:31.455
It wouldn't be the worst thing
to leave this place.

04:31.455 --> 04:33.790
Nate, my mother
was wronged.
I know.

04:33.790 --> 04:36.426
And wanting revenge
feels natural.

04:36.426 --> 04:37.727
Noble.
Yep.

04:37.727 --> 04:40.364
But trust me, Gee.
It can destroy you.

04:43.099 --> 04:44.801
My first few years
in prison,

04:44.801 --> 04:47.103
I fantasized about
what I would do to the guy

04:47.103 --> 04:49.305
that actually shot
and killed that security guard.

04:49.305 --> 04:51.808
We said, "No guns."
He brought one anyway.

04:51.808 --> 04:53.610
And just like that,
my future,

04:53.610 --> 04:55.745
my family,
everything was gone.

04:55.745 --> 04:57.246
I wanted to pay him back,
Gee,

04:57.246 --> 05:00.249
and that anger and that
hatred -- it took holda' me.

05:00.249 --> 05:04.654
And it kept me in a toxic place
in the past.

05:04.654 --> 05:07.056
You have a bright future
ahead of you.

05:07.056 --> 05:10.093
With Nikki, with everything
you are doing with Eve's Crown.

05:10.093 --> 05:13.663
Why not put all of your energy
into that?

05:13.663 --> 05:15.732
Do that
in your mom's name.

05:17.401 --> 05:19.436
[ Sniffles ]

05:23.607 --> 05:25.341
Beads.

05:25.341 --> 05:31.915
**

05:31.915 --> 05:38.455
**

05:38.455 --> 05:42.426
Mr. Dupont, your signature
is needed on these right away.

05:42.426 --> 05:45.028
You know what these are,
don't you?

05:45.028 --> 05:47.196
These are
the transfer documents

05:47.196 --> 05:49.699
that will return
Jack's Darmon shares

05:49.699 --> 05:51.635
back to their
rightful place.

05:51.635 --> 05:53.169
With me.

05:53.169 --> 05:55.439
I do hate the fact that
my business partner's death

05:55.439 --> 05:58.041
made these mine again,
but, oh, well.

05:58.041 --> 05:59.208
Winning is winning.

05:59.208 --> 06:01.545
And gloating
is for dilettantes.

06:01.545 --> 06:05.114
Look, we've been going
through this for years.

06:05.114 --> 06:06.783
You've never liked me,
and I'm okay with that.

06:06.783 --> 06:08.017
This is not
about feelings.

06:08.017 --> 06:10.954
This is about business,
about legacy,

06:10.954 --> 06:12.321
about leaving behind

06:12.321 --> 06:15.291
a solid foundation
to build upon.

06:15.291 --> 06:17.494
Well, whether you like it
or not, we're family.

06:17.494 --> 06:20.530
Hurting me hurts your daughter,
hurts your grandkids.

06:20.530 --> 06:21.998
But you know what?

06:21.998 --> 06:24.067
You have that ego
to where you need to snuff out

06:24.067 --> 06:26.135
the ones you love
to make you feel like the man.

06:26.135 --> 06:28.071
And you want
to call me weak.

06:28.071 --> 06:29.573
All you do
is hide behind your money.

06:29.573 --> 06:31.541
You dangle a carrot
in front of your own daughter

06:31.541 --> 06:33.677
to buy her love.

06:33.677 --> 06:35.011
You hid your wife away

06:35.011 --> 06:37.847
because you couldn't
handle her illness.

06:37.847 --> 06:40.517
Now look at you.

06:40.517 --> 06:43.419
[ Chuckles ]
You want to call me weak.

06:43.419 --> 06:45.589
All of that...
is weak as hell.

06:45.589 --> 06:48.925
And this is why I prefer
taking breakfast in my suite.

06:49.993 --> 06:52.596
You may own
Jack's shares.

06:52.596 --> 06:53.830
I own the company.

06:53.830 --> 06:55.164
For now.

06:55.164 --> 06:57.567
This is only
the first step.

06:57.567 --> 06:59.736
**

06:59.736 --> 07:02.371
You keep thinking that.

07:02.371 --> 07:04.841
You didn't make it
to breakfast.

07:04.841 --> 07:06.242
Yeah.

07:06.242 --> 07:07.677
Um...

07:07.677 --> 07:09.445
I guess
I wasn't hungry.

07:09.445 --> 07:12.248
Still thinking about
what you did to Angela?

07:12.248 --> 07:13.249
Yes.

07:13.249 --> 07:15.952
But you could be
more gentle.

07:15.952 --> 07:18.221
Right now you are
in a bad place with Angela

07:18.221 --> 07:19.589
because of what
your father did.

07:19.589 --> 07:22.391
Made you spy on her.
Hold back information.

07:22.391 --> 07:24.961
And you blocked
her every move.

07:24.961 --> 07:26.295
Okay, I know you
don't believe this,

07:26.295 --> 07:29.098
but he really is
just trying to protect me.

07:29.098 --> 07:30.634
And, more importantly,
my mother.

07:30.634 --> 07:33.537
Sweetheart, the only person
Teddy Franklin protects

07:33.537 --> 07:34.771
is Teddy Franklin.

07:34.771 --> 07:37.473
He lies and manipulates
everybody in his path.

07:37.473 --> 07:40.977
And the only reason
why he keeps you fat and happy

07:40.977 --> 07:42.879
is 'cause you don't
call him on it.

07:42.879 --> 07:44.080
Wow, babe.

07:44.080 --> 07:46.149
This has been one hell
of a pep talk.

07:46.149 --> 07:47.416
Okay, hold on.
Hold on, hold on.

07:47.416 --> 07:48.985
How about this?

07:48.985 --> 07:53.823
How about you quit
Franklin Holdings...

07:53.823 --> 07:55.725
and we run Darmon
together?

07:55.725 --> 07:57.827
Full partners.

07:57.827 --> 07:59.328
[ Chuckles ]

07:59.328 --> 08:00.664
Raymond, that's not
even an option.

08:00.664 --> 08:03.900
It will be when I get
the company back.

08:03.900 --> 08:05.635
Baby,
the two of us together --

08:05.635 --> 08:07.003
we would be unstoppable.

08:07.003 --> 08:09.639
Darmon needs it.
You deserve it.

08:09.639 --> 08:11.675
A real partnership.

08:11.675 --> 08:12.842
What do you say?

08:12.842 --> 08:20.784
**

08:20.784 --> 08:22.485
I miss your face.

08:22.485 --> 08:24.187
Taylor: You're looking
at it, goof.

08:24.187 --> 08:27.591
[ Chuckles ]
I mean in person.

08:27.591 --> 08:29.826
Something crazy is happening
with my aunt,

08:29.826 --> 08:32.028
and, um...

08:32.028 --> 08:34.598
Maybe we can go get ices
at Mira's later today?

08:34.598 --> 08:37.033
Yeah.
Just let me know when.

08:37.033 --> 08:38.868
Thanks.

08:38.868 --> 08:41.370
And, um, Tay?

08:43.039 --> 08:44.874
I love you.
Aww, babe.

08:44.874 --> 08:46.175
I'll catch you soon,
okay?

08:46.175 --> 08:48.144
[ Cellphone chimes ]

08:48.144 --> 08:49.278
* I watch you

08:49.278 --> 08:50.814
[ Sighs ]
That was awkward.

08:50.814 --> 08:52.481
You feel awkward?

08:52.481 --> 08:54.550
I'm the one cheating
on my girlfriend.

08:54.550 --> 08:56.052
Is it really cheating, though,
if you're literally

08:56.052 --> 08:57.220
just sleeping
with your ex?

08:57.220 --> 08:58.622
Pretty sure it is.

08:58.622 --> 09:00.857
And we did more than sleep
that first night.

09:00.857 --> 09:03.492
Right, but...

09:03.492 --> 09:05.629
I mean, seeing Uncle Jack
freaked us both out.

09:05.629 --> 09:07.363
And I'm not saying
that it's right,

09:07.363 --> 09:10.466
but we were just making each
other feel better in the moment.

09:10.466 --> 09:11.668
Yeah.

09:11.668 --> 09:14.303
* Even when you're no good
for me *

09:14.303 --> 09:16.572
Even now,
when I close my eyes...

09:16.572 --> 09:18.708
You can still see him.

09:18.708 --> 09:20.744
I know.

09:20.744 --> 09:23.212
[ Sighs ] I got to
break up with her.

09:23.212 --> 09:24.681
What?
Yeah.

09:24.681 --> 09:25.715
N-No.

09:25.715 --> 09:27.383
Please don't do that.
What?

09:27.383 --> 09:29.719
Like you said, right now,
emotions are running high.

09:29.719 --> 09:31.020
And you and I are just --

09:31.020 --> 09:32.255
we're helping each other
through a rough patch.

09:32.255 --> 09:33.657
It's like we have some --

09:33.657 --> 09:35.524
I don't know --
some sort of trauma bond.

09:35.524 --> 09:37.360
We have a bond,
period.

09:37.360 --> 09:39.095
We were
each other's first.

09:39.095 --> 09:42.098
You and I fit together.

09:42.098 --> 09:44.768
When you're in my arms,
it feels right,

09:44.768 --> 09:47.036
and I...

09:47.036 --> 09:49.105
I don't want anybody else.

09:49.105 --> 09:52.108
* What you did

09:52.108 --> 09:56.045
* And it feels
just like murder *

09:56.045 --> 09:58.047
* Killin' me, killin' me

09:58.047 --> 09:59.282
I'm not going anywhere.

09:59.282 --> 10:01.450
* Killin' me softly

10:01.450 --> 10:03.452
* Killin' me,
killin' me softly *

10:03.452 --> 10:05.521
I actually can't believe
I'm saying this, but...

10:05.521 --> 10:07.390
[ Scoffs ]

10:07.390 --> 10:09.092
I actually care
about Nikki's feelings,

10:09.092 --> 10:10.960
and I don't want her heart
to get broken.

10:10.960 --> 10:12.896
* I watch you cut me down

10:12.896 --> 10:15.464
I --
We're finally in, like,

10:15.464 --> 10:19.235
this really good place
as cousins and...

10:19.235 --> 10:21.604
* Still I keep marching
right on back *

10:21.604 --> 10:24.908
Tay, all I'm asking for
is just a little bit more time

10:24.908 --> 10:27.310
for us to break the news
to her.

10:27.310 --> 10:29.946
* I could really use somebody

10:29.946 --> 10:31.280
What is going on?

10:31.280 --> 10:33.717
I thought that this
is what you wanted.

10:33.717 --> 10:35.318
You would always tell me,
"Be nice to the girl."

10:35.318 --> 10:37.987
I'm being nice.

10:37.987 --> 10:40.289
Fine.

10:40.289 --> 10:42.325
It's just weird
that being "nice"

10:42.325 --> 10:44.928
is making me
feel this bad.

10:44.928 --> 10:46.830
* Erase what you did

10:46.830 --> 10:51.000
* And it feels
just like murder *

10:51.000 --> 10:53.336
* Killin' me, killin' me

10:53.336 --> 10:55.171
Eve: I had dreams, baby.

10:55.171 --> 10:58.441
I had a small salon, and I was
gonna make it something big.

10:58.441 --> 10:59.776
Little Angela:
Mama, don't cry.

10:59.776 --> 11:02.478
I'm done crying.
It's on you now.

11:02.478 --> 11:04.347
**

11:04.347 --> 11:07.851
[ Door opens, closes ]

11:08.818 --> 11:10.686
[ Sighs ]

11:12.655 --> 11:15.191
Angela,
I want to explain

11:15.191 --> 11:17.160
why I voted you out
of the Graceties.

11:17.160 --> 11:18.627
I know why.

11:18.627 --> 11:20.864
Your daddy
made you do it.

11:25.601 --> 11:29.205
Your agenda was gonna end up
hurting my mother.

11:29.205 --> 11:30.974
Leah...

11:30.974 --> 11:33.877
my mother is dead,
okay?

11:33.877 --> 11:36.379
It took everything in me
to scatter her ashes

11:36.379 --> 11:38.114
in a place
that broke her heart.

11:38.114 --> 11:41.851
Your mother's alive and well.
I hope you're grateful for that.

11:41.851 --> 11:44.220
Anyway...

11:44.220 --> 11:46.389
[ Sighs ]
I get it now.

11:46.389 --> 11:48.124
No matter
how hard I push,

11:48.124 --> 11:49.392
I cannot find answers

11:49.392 --> 11:52.395
'cause you are
gonna block me.

11:52.395 --> 11:55.398
So just stop pretending

11:55.398 --> 11:58.968
that you care about me,
that the sisterhood is real.

11:58.968 --> 12:00.169
Go.

12:00.169 --> 12:01.805
Tell your father
we have a deal.

12:01.805 --> 12:04.740
I'll leave the Bluffs for good.
I'll take his seed money.

12:04.740 --> 12:07.243
Oh, what, you gonna act
like you didn't know?

12:07.243 --> 12:08.912
I didn't.

12:08.912 --> 12:10.313
Well, you do now.

12:10.313 --> 12:12.715
As for you and me,

12:12.715 --> 12:15.251
I don't see a reason for us
to see each other again.

12:15.251 --> 12:22.591
**

12:22.591 --> 12:29.498
**

12:29.498 --> 12:34.237
[ Door opens, closes ]

12:35.604 --> 12:36.940
[ Sighs ]

12:40.676 --> 12:43.579
**

12:43.579 --> 12:46.449
Her name is Patricia Vaughn.
She went in last night.

12:46.449 --> 12:49.052
I just need to know
that she's okay.

12:49.052 --> 12:50.286
[ Door opens ]
Yes, I'll hold.

12:50.286 --> 12:51.454
Maybe we should just
go down there.

12:51.454 --> 12:53.756
I wanted to,
but Teddy --

12:53.756 --> 12:54.958
[ Gasps ]

12:54.958 --> 12:56.259
Piggy!

12:57.460 --> 13:00.196
Oh.
Are you okay?

13:00.196 --> 13:02.565
Yeah.
I'm just tired.

13:07.470 --> 13:08.804
I guess you
can't say Teddy

13:08.804 --> 13:10.239
doesn't hold up
his end of the bargain.

13:10.239 --> 13:12.608
What is that
supposed to mean?

13:12.608 --> 13:16.312
I asked him
to pull some strings.

13:16.312 --> 13:17.580
He didn't pull crap.

13:17.580 --> 13:19.048
This whole time,
I've been in a room

13:19.048 --> 13:22.251
with two detectives
confessing my heart out.

13:22.251 --> 13:23.752
But when you walk in
off the street

13:23.752 --> 13:26.222
and admit to a murder
from 30-plus years ago,

13:26.222 --> 13:27.623
that ain't enough
for an arrest.

13:27.623 --> 13:30.493
They let me go
pending an investigation.

13:30.493 --> 13:33.829
Until they find Darius' body,
I'm a free woman.

13:33.829 --> 13:35.298
Waiting for a shoe
like that to drop

13:35.298 --> 13:36.599
doesn't sound very "free,"
Piggy.

13:36.599 --> 13:39.335
Oh, it does to me,
baby girl.

13:39.335 --> 13:41.971
I prayed on this,

13:41.971 --> 13:44.673
and my heart is right.

13:44.673 --> 13:46.509
My burden
has been lifted.

13:46.509 --> 13:48.344
Now, you said "bargain."

13:48.344 --> 13:50.346
What did that snake Teddy
ask you to do?

13:50.346 --> 13:52.015
He said he would help

13:52.015 --> 13:55.418
only if I agreed to leave
the island for good.

13:55.418 --> 13:58.254
And what about finding out
what happened to your mama?

13:58.254 --> 13:59.655
Look, Piggy,
I don't know

13:59.655 --> 14:01.024
what's gonna come
of this investigation.

14:01.024 --> 14:03.859
I just wanted to make sure
that we had

14:03.859 --> 14:06.629
all of Teddy's connections
at our disposal.

14:06.629 --> 14:08.597
I want you
to listen to me.

14:08.597 --> 14:10.466
Now, I'm not gonna
let you give up

14:10.466 --> 14:12.835
clearing your mama's name
to protect me.

14:12.835 --> 14:14.270
I will serve my time.

14:14.270 --> 14:15.972
And all we need to do now

14:15.972 --> 14:18.975
is enjoy our time together
while we have it.

14:18.975 --> 14:20.509
Oh, come on, now.

14:20.509 --> 14:22.811
Ain't nothing to cry about
but taxes.

14:22.811 --> 14:24.847
[ Chuckles ]
Now, we're gonna celebrate.

14:24.847 --> 14:26.482
And I don't know
about you two,

14:26.482 --> 14:30.719
but I'm gonna give myself
a grand throw-down barbecue

14:30.719 --> 14:34.057
with all our old friends
before I go away, okay?

14:34.057 --> 14:36.559
And all I want you two to do
is smile, dance,

14:36.559 --> 14:38.561
and maybe get
a little faded.

14:38.561 --> 14:40.063
Not you, baby girl.

14:40.063 --> 14:42.465
Well, we Vaughn women do know
how to throw down.

14:42.465 --> 14:43.566
Mm-hmm,
yes, we do.

14:43.566 --> 14:46.735
I say let's do it today,
alright?

14:46.735 --> 14:50.073
Let's give me the best
"farewell" ever.

14:50.073 --> 14:52.008
Alright.

14:52.008 --> 14:57.246
**

14:57.246 --> 14:58.881
So, everybody thought
we were gonna do the waltz,

14:58.881 --> 15:00.316
but we had
something else planned.

15:00.316 --> 15:01.550
We even got
the DJ involved.

15:01.550 --> 15:03.186
Quincy: Grandma,
they were not ready.

15:03.186 --> 15:04.553
I'm telling you.

15:04.553 --> 15:06.889
Rose: Oh, look at that!
That was you upside down.

15:06.889 --> 15:09.858
That was me.
You kids are so clever.

15:09.858 --> 15:11.327
What do you think you'd have
done if you were there?

15:11.327 --> 15:12.595
I probably
would have fainted.

15:12.595 --> 15:14.563
You would
have loved it.

15:14.563 --> 15:15.564
Jackie: Here you go.

15:15.564 --> 15:16.832
Thank you, Jackie.

15:16.832 --> 15:19.035
Patrick,
take her luggage upstairs.

15:19.035 --> 15:20.869
Leah: Well, you have to see
Olivia's reaction.

15:20.869 --> 15:22.738
She almost fell
off the podium.

15:22.738 --> 15:24.207
Lauren: That may have been the
best part of the whole thing.

15:24.207 --> 15:25.774
Quincy: So mad.
Oh, Daddy!

15:25.774 --> 15:28.344
Why don't you come on in
and give your wife a hug?

15:28.344 --> 15:29.612
Hi, Granddaddy.
Hey, Grandpa.

15:29.612 --> 15:31.280
How's it going, Lauren?
Good. How are you?

15:31.280 --> 15:32.948
I'm alright.

15:34.450 --> 15:36.452
Thought I would come home
and help Leah

15:36.452 --> 15:38.121
prep for
the Grand Illumination week.

15:38.121 --> 15:40.423
Hmm.
You know how special
that night is to me.

15:40.423 --> 15:42.791
Yeah, I know.

15:42.791 --> 15:44.893
Uh, Leah,
can I, um...

15:44.893 --> 15:46.262
Yeah.

15:46.262 --> 15:50.066
So, we started it in, like,
two rows, right? And I...

15:50.066 --> 15:51.200
Why is your mother here?

15:51.200 --> 15:52.635
She called and said
she wanted to be a part

15:52.635 --> 15:54.537
of the Grand Illumination
festivities.

15:54.537 --> 15:55.771
Her doctors signed off.

15:55.771 --> 15:57.640
She's taking her meds.
And look at her.

15:57.640 --> 16:00.376
I mean, she hasn't been
this lucid or energetic

16:00.376 --> 16:01.710
in a really long time.

16:01.710 --> 16:03.279
You should have consulted
with me first.

16:03.279 --> 16:07.250
Why? You didn't consult with me
before offering Angela a deal.

16:07.250 --> 16:08.617
And she's taking it,
by the way.

16:08.617 --> 16:10.486
Then we're almost finished.

16:10.486 --> 16:11.887
Just like that?
Mm-hmm.

16:11.887 --> 16:14.790
Yeah, well, I'm having
a harder time with it.

16:14.790 --> 16:17.660
When you told me to torpedo
her Graceties membership,

16:17.660 --> 16:20.763
you destroyed any hope
of us becoming real sisters.

16:20.763 --> 16:23.566
We all have to make sacrifices
to protect the family.

16:23.566 --> 16:25.668
Right.
And what are your sacrifices?

16:25.668 --> 16:27.770
I'm losing
a daughter again.

16:27.770 --> 16:30.439
That you're
pushing out.

16:30.439 --> 16:31.740
You know,
Raymond accused you

16:31.740 --> 16:33.276
of keeping me fat and happy
to control me.

16:33.276 --> 16:35.144
Is that what you think?
I'm protecting your mother.

16:35.144 --> 16:38.181
But you could hardly hug her
or greet her.

16:38.181 --> 16:40.183
I mean, if this is all
about protecting Mommy,

16:40.183 --> 16:42.685
then she can stay in this house,
her home,

16:42.685 --> 16:45.921
for as long as she wants,
and I'm gonna be there for her.

16:45.921 --> 16:47.690
Ruining my relationship
with Angela

16:47.690 --> 16:50.025
has got to be worth something,
right, Daddy?

16:50.025 --> 16:54.163
**

16:54.163 --> 16:56.199
Raymond: And this morning,
Teddy had no choice

16:56.199 --> 16:59.034
but to watch those shares
come right back to me.

16:59.034 --> 17:00.803
The first of
many battles won.

17:00.803 --> 17:02.838
Well played.
How are things on your end?

17:02.838 --> 17:04.273
Well, you know
how you said you and Leah

17:04.273 --> 17:06.209
are locked out of the
Our Legacy files?

17:06.209 --> 17:08.844
Thanks to my new gig designing
the skyboxes for Teddy,

17:08.844 --> 17:11.680
IT has hooked me up
with the login and password

17:11.680 --> 17:12.948
for Franklin Holdings.

17:12.948 --> 17:14.383
I think I can back-door it,
get in,

17:14.383 --> 17:15.851
and see what
he's been hiding.

17:15.851 --> 17:19.722
And I can get my company back
and my wife free and I --

17:19.722 --> 17:21.824
It's scary how
he has her played.

17:21.824 --> 17:23.058
She doesn't see it,

17:23.058 --> 17:25.027
but I'm gonna show her
who he really is.

17:25.027 --> 17:26.729
Hey, you gotta fight
for the woman you love.

17:26.729 --> 17:27.963
Speaking of which,
you and Angela --

17:27.963 --> 17:29.665
you guys got something going,
right?

17:29.665 --> 17:32.235
Yeah.
I might've messed that up.

17:32.235 --> 17:35.204
And now she's got her ex
hanging around, so...

17:35.204 --> 17:37.206
Wait, you talking about
her baby's father

17:37.206 --> 17:39.007
that lives with her?
Yeah.

17:39.007 --> 17:40.709
That's more than
hanging around.

17:40.709 --> 17:42.745
Alright, alright, I'm --
I'm getting back in the fight.

17:42.745 --> 17:44.079
I just hate
to take down a brother

17:44.079 --> 17:45.548
that just got home,
but --

17:45.548 --> 17:48.016
You can't win
if you don't battle.

17:48.016 --> 17:51.019
To winning the battle
and the war.

17:51.019 --> 17:52.555
**

17:52.555 --> 17:56.024
* Lord, forgive me

17:56.024 --> 17:57.860
* For the things
that I'm doin' *

17:57.860 --> 18:01.264
* You're lookin' for,
you're lookin' for that money *

18:04.099 --> 18:06.735
You're not like
these other girls.

18:06.735 --> 18:08.237
Are you using lines
on me now?

18:08.237 --> 18:10.906
No.
I'm serious.

18:10.906 --> 18:12.841
Look, I don't know why
I waste my time

18:12.841 --> 18:16.111
with these bougie princesses
when you're real.

18:21.284 --> 18:23.386
[ Clears throat ]

18:23.386 --> 18:26.422
So, Mariah Treadwell's bag
was stolen from her Beach Party.

18:26.422 --> 18:29.124
Um, and it's oxblood red,
so it's, like, super rare.

18:29.124 --> 18:30.293
Seen it?

18:30.293 --> 18:34.062
So the maid's granddaughter
must've taken it?

18:34.062 --> 18:34.930
Way to be basic.

18:34.930 --> 18:36.699
Not as basic
as gold-digging.

18:36.699 --> 18:38.634
Lo, relax.

18:38.634 --> 18:40.569
I've been watching this girl
for a week,

18:40.569 --> 18:42.905
and she is on you
like it's her damn job.

18:42.905 --> 18:44.640
So what?
Is this your summer job,
Sloane?

18:44.640 --> 18:46.141
My brother?

18:47.943 --> 18:50.112
You know, you should be more
like your friend Taylor.

18:50.112 --> 18:52.648
I like her.
She's nice.

18:52.648 --> 18:54.817
Oh, and by the way,

18:54.817 --> 18:57.220
tell her I love
those kicks she was wearing.

18:57.220 --> 19:01.056
Does Nikki know y'all
have been kicking it?

19:01.056 --> 19:02.658
Have you been
spying on us?

19:02.658 --> 19:05.160
I was cleaning the upstairs
hallway when you walked her out.

19:05.160 --> 19:06.829
Of course
you didn't notice.

19:06.829 --> 19:09.498
I mean, the help is invisible
to girls like you.

19:09.498 --> 19:11.834
Q doesn't know
your business.

19:11.834 --> 19:14.337
But I suggest
you stay out of mine.

19:14.337 --> 19:20.976
**

19:24.580 --> 19:26.181
[ Door opens ]

19:26.181 --> 19:27.416
Ah, Brooks.

19:27.416 --> 19:28.617
I need your services.

19:28.617 --> 19:30.419
You're the best investigator
I know.

19:30.419 --> 19:35.157
My son-in-law is trying
to acquire some shares

19:35.157 --> 19:37.960
as a result of the demise
of his business partner

19:37.960 --> 19:41.297
with whom I struck a deal
for those same shares.

19:41.297 --> 19:44.300
The contract
mysteriously disappeared.

19:44.300 --> 19:46.869
I would like you to look
into Jack Harmon's death,

19:46.869 --> 19:48.837
which has been ruled
as accidental.

19:48.837 --> 19:51.274
Find something
that would force the police

19:51.274 --> 19:53.342
to re-open the case.

19:53.342 --> 19:57.680
Pay close attention
to the actions of my son-in-law.

19:57.680 --> 19:59.147
I don't trust him.

19:59.147 --> 20:02.050
If I can get Jack's death ruled
as suspicious,

20:02.050 --> 20:05.654
it will stall the transfer
of Jack's shares to Raymond.

20:05.654 --> 20:06.789
I'm on it, Boss.

20:06.789 --> 20:08.190
Excellent.

20:08.190 --> 20:09.625
Oh,
and -- and one more thing.

20:09.625 --> 20:11.294
I promised to help
Patricia Vaughn.

20:11.294 --> 20:14.663
So I need something delivered
to Eve's Crown.

20:14.663 --> 20:17.800
**

20:17.800 --> 20:19.535
Thank you.

20:19.535 --> 20:25.808
**

20:25.808 --> 20:27.075
Checkmate.

20:27.976 --> 20:31.480
So, this is the dress
that you were inducted in?

20:31.480 --> 20:32.681
Rose: Mm-hmm.

20:32.681 --> 20:34.917
It is exquisite.
[ Chuckles ]

20:34.917 --> 20:36.485
I mean,
what do you think?

20:36.485 --> 20:38.053
I mean, probably have to drop
the hem a little bit, right?

20:38.053 --> 20:40.989
Mm, wear it and all eyes
will be on you,

20:40.989 --> 20:43.559
as they should,
Madame President.

20:43.559 --> 20:48.163
You are about to usher women
into a beautiful sisterhood.

20:50.666 --> 20:53.569
Leah,
is something wrong?

20:53.569 --> 20:56.271
Um, Ashley, will you give us
a minute, please?

21:01.009 --> 21:02.511
There is one sister

21:02.511 --> 21:04.279
who should be there --

21:04.279 --> 21:06.949
my sister,
Angela Vaughn.

21:06.949 --> 21:08.351
And, Mommy, I'm sorry.

21:08.351 --> 21:10.386
I know that name brings up
painful memories for you,

21:10.386 --> 21:14.423
but now Daddy wants her gone
to protect the family.

21:14.423 --> 21:17.960
And I don't even know
what that means.

21:17.960 --> 21:20.529
Can you tell me why?

21:20.529 --> 21:26.535
Your father and I
have so many secrets.

21:26.535 --> 21:28.203
And I'm sorry
if our past

21:28.203 --> 21:30.373
is making our present
that much harder.

21:30.373 --> 21:33.542
I've always made your life
that much harder.

21:33.542 --> 21:37.413
And that's why I called
to come home before the ball,

21:37.413 --> 21:41.484
to be here with you
for your big day --

21:41.484 --> 21:45.320
to tell you that I love you,
my beautiful baby girl.

21:46.889 --> 21:51.126
I want to have a good memory
with you...

21:51.126 --> 21:53.496
even if it's
just this one.

21:53.496 --> 21:56.832
There are gonna be
plenty more, Mommy.

21:56.832 --> 22:01.904
**

22:01.904 --> 22:03.506
I promise.

22:03.506 --> 22:07.443
**

22:07.443 --> 22:10.245
[ Upbeat music plays,
indistinct conversations ]

22:10.245 --> 22:12.748
**

22:12.748 --> 22:14.683
You was right.
You was right.

22:14.683 --> 22:16.519
We needed this.

22:16.519 --> 22:18.253
Go big...

22:18.253 --> 22:20.956
and then take my ass
to the big house.

22:20.956 --> 22:22.324
[ Chuckles ]

22:22.324 --> 22:23.792
* Put your left foot
to the front *

22:23.792 --> 22:27.630
Oh, that's my ish!
[ Laughs ]

22:27.630 --> 22:29.131
Let's show 'em, ladies.

22:29.131 --> 22:30.466
* Shake like you're having
an attack *

22:30.466 --> 22:32.000
* Jiggle, jiggle,
jiggle, jiggle *

22:32.000 --> 22:33.536
* Jiggle, jiggle,
jiggle, jiggle *

22:33.536 --> 22:35.504
* When you dance on the floor,
do the jiggle *

22:35.504 --> 22:37.139
* Jiggle, jiggle,
jiggle, jiggle *

22:37.139 --> 22:38.541
* Jiggle, jiggle, jiggle

22:38.541 --> 22:40.509
* Don't stop this flow,
do the jiggle *

22:40.509 --> 22:43.446
* At the party got to do
what counts *

22:43.446 --> 22:45.614
* Big cash coming
in large amounts *

22:45.614 --> 22:48.216
* I don't wanna see you shake,
make it bounce *

22:48.216 --> 22:50.385
* 'Cause that's what
a dancing party's all about *

22:50.385 --> 22:52.988
* At the party got to do
what counts *

22:52.988 --> 22:55.491
* Big cash coming
in large amounts *

22:55.491 --> 22:57.793
* I don't wanna see you shake,
make it bounce *

22:57.793 --> 23:00.295
* 'Cause that's what
a dancing party's all about *

23:00.295 --> 23:01.864
* Put your left foot
to the front *

23:01.864 --> 23:03.365
Tyrique: Hey.
Hey!

23:03.365 --> 23:04.967
Y'all got it
poppin' in here.

23:04.967 --> 23:06.401
This is better
than my parties.

23:06.401 --> 23:08.370
Oh, get over here.

23:08.370 --> 23:10.038
* Shake like you're having
an attack *

23:10.038 --> 23:11.406
Look what I got.

23:11.406 --> 23:13.642
* Put your left foot
to the front *

23:13.642 --> 23:17.412
Now, you need to
put some stank on this.

23:17.412 --> 23:20.248
You need to mind
your business.

23:20.248 --> 23:22.918
[ Chuckles ] Listen,
if I don't mind your business,

23:22.918 --> 23:24.520
I don't know who will.

23:24.520 --> 23:26.655
Now, I know that you two
got work to do,

23:26.655 --> 23:29.525
but don't forget that I was
there when you first met.

23:29.525 --> 23:31.393
And I saw how you looked
at each other.

23:31.393 --> 23:35.330
That kind of kismet is so rare,
so beautiful.

23:35.330 --> 23:38.266
Black love and all
that good stuff.

23:38.266 --> 23:40.102
* Put your right foot
to the back *

23:40.102 --> 23:43.005
I, um --
I do feel responsible

23:43.005 --> 23:44.940
for getting in the way
of all that.

23:44.940 --> 23:47.042
I mean, if I had just
come clean earlier

23:47.042 --> 23:50.412
and given you the closure
that you needed, Tyrique,

23:50.412 --> 23:53.749
maybe there wouldn't be so much
distance between you two.

23:53.749 --> 23:55.350
Yeah, well,
don't feel that way.

23:55.350 --> 23:58.521
I take responsibility for
the missteps me and Angela have.

23:58.521 --> 24:00.523
Just hope
it's not too late.

24:00.523 --> 24:03.792
Alright,
make the earth quake, people!

24:03.792 --> 24:05.193
[ Cheers and applause ]

24:05.193 --> 24:07.362
* At the party got to do
what counts *

24:07.362 --> 24:09.598
* Big cash coming
in large amounts *

24:09.598 --> 24:12.234
* I don't wanna see you shake,
make it bounce *

24:12.234 --> 24:14.402
* 'Cause that's what
a dancing party's all about *

24:14.402 --> 24:17.272
* At the party got to do
what counts *

24:17.272 --> 24:19.708
* Big cash coming
in large amounts *

24:19.708 --> 24:22.077
[ Tense music plays ]

24:22.077 --> 24:27.650
**

24:27.650 --> 24:33.055
**

24:33.055 --> 24:35.057
Darius?

24:35.891 --> 24:37.225
Hello, Patricia.

24:42.631 --> 24:44.600
Piggy: 30-plus years,

24:44.600 --> 24:46.468
and you let me think
you were dead.

24:46.468 --> 24:48.671
That's what we wanted you
to believe.

24:48.671 --> 24:51.406
Who's we?
Me and Teddy Franklin.

24:51.406 --> 24:53.809
After you stabbed me,
I passed out --

24:53.809 --> 24:55.410
partly from the blood loss,

24:55.410 --> 24:57.946
partly from all the drugs
I had in my system.

24:57.946 --> 24:59.481
When I woke up,
Teddy was there.

24:59.481 --> 25:01.483
Eve said her boss
could help me.

25:01.483 --> 25:04.252
And he knew how much Eve
wanted you to get clean,

25:04.252 --> 25:06.088
so I guess he figured
the best way to do that

25:06.088 --> 25:07.923
was to have you think
that I was dead.

25:07.923 --> 25:10.492
I guess the bastard
was right.

25:10.492 --> 25:13.361
Because the guilt that I carried
around after that night

25:13.361 --> 25:16.131
is what finally
drove me to N.A.

25:16.131 --> 25:17.365
Why are you here now?

25:17.365 --> 25:20.168
Someone from Teddy's camp
reached out,

25:20.168 --> 25:22.638
said that Patricia turned
herself in for my murder,

25:22.638 --> 25:25.207
and that I should get down
to the police station myself

25:25.207 --> 25:26.642
and clear this up.

25:26.642 --> 25:28.176
Then after that,
I was supposed to come here

25:28.176 --> 25:30.012
so you could see me
with your own eyes.

25:30.012 --> 25:31.780
I can still barely
believe it.

25:31.780 --> 25:34.149
And our last night together,
I was at my worst.

25:34.149 --> 25:36.218
High outta my mind
on them drugs.

25:36.218 --> 25:38.520
Laying hands on the woman
I loved.

25:38.520 --> 25:41.289
When you stabbed me,
that should've ended it for me.

25:41.289 --> 25:43.491
Instead, it gave me
a new beginning,

25:43.491 --> 25:46.161
helped me put my life
back on track.

25:46.161 --> 25:50.132
So I sincerely hope that,
after today,

25:50.132 --> 25:51.967
you get a new beginning,
too.

25:51.967 --> 25:53.702
[ Chuckles ]

25:53.702 --> 25:56.972
**

25:56.972 --> 26:00.308
Oh, oh, Lord.

26:00.308 --> 26:02.678
Thank you
for setting me free.

26:02.678 --> 26:06.048
And, I guess, I thank you,
Teddy Franklin.

26:06.048 --> 26:12.254
**

26:15.891 --> 26:17.926
Why are you so rude?

26:17.926 --> 26:20.896
What?
Lo, I like her.

26:20.896 --> 26:22.330
So you need
to fall back.

26:22.330 --> 26:23.999
[ Laughs ] Okay.

26:23.999 --> 26:25.333
Q, I'm your twin.

26:25.333 --> 26:26.568
I know you better
than other people do.

26:26.568 --> 26:29.204
Sloane's not it.
That girl threatened me.

26:29.204 --> 26:31.173
You act like you own me,
Lo,

26:31.173 --> 26:33.041
like you get a say
in what I do.

26:33.041 --> 26:34.276
You don't.

26:34.276 --> 26:35.878
Anytime I get something
for me, you --

26:35.878 --> 26:38.747
y-you see it as a threat
a-and you try to blow it up

26:38.747 --> 26:40.716
'cause you're selfish
and you're controlling.

26:40.716 --> 26:42.517
And I'm getting sick of it.
You know what?

26:42.517 --> 26:44.519
I was trying to be nice
about the whole Sloane thing,

26:44.519 --> 26:46.054
but here are the facts.

26:46.054 --> 26:48.390
The only reason you like Sloane
is because she's poor,

26:48.390 --> 26:50.525
which, honestly,
I-I don't get that.

26:50.525 --> 26:51.860
But you are
going to drop her

26:51.860 --> 26:54.362
like you drop everything else
in your life.

26:54.362 --> 26:56.364
I would be surprised
if this relationship

26:56.364 --> 26:58.901
lasted more than
two weeks, tops.

26:58.901 --> 27:00.535
I feel bad for Sloane

27:00.535 --> 27:03.205
'cause that girl doesn't even
know what's coming to her.

27:05.273 --> 27:07.042
There's something wrong
with you.

27:07.042 --> 27:11.079
**

27:11.079 --> 27:12.715
[ Door closes ]

27:21.556 --> 27:23.325
[ Chime ]

27:25.794 --> 27:28.230
Oh.

27:39.241 --> 27:41.944
Excuse me, milady.

27:41.944 --> 27:44.479
Can I have this dance?

27:44.479 --> 27:48.817
* Rules are made to be broken

27:48.817 --> 27:50.185
* Baby

27:50.185 --> 27:53.121
* I'm breakin' all my rules

27:53.121 --> 27:54.522
* For you

27:54.522 --> 27:58.360
I apologize for my coldness
towards you earlier.

27:58.360 --> 28:00.495
Now you just hush.

28:00.495 --> 28:04.266
This piece was playing
during our first waltz

28:04.266 --> 28:07.135
at the Grand Illumination Ball
in 1984.

28:07.135 --> 28:08.203
I remember.

28:08.203 --> 28:09.537
* Now my mother

28:09.537 --> 28:12.140
And this is a hard time of year
for me.

28:12.140 --> 28:14.810
Of course it is.

28:14.810 --> 28:16.111
For me as well.

28:16.111 --> 28:17.445
* To make sure they're strong

28:17.445 --> 28:20.348
* But you mustn't give in

28:20.348 --> 28:21.784
* I know, I know, I know

28:21.784 --> 28:24.286
I'm so sorry.

28:24.286 --> 28:25.788
I destroyed our family,

28:25.788 --> 28:28.957
and I am doing everything I can
to make up for it.

28:28.957 --> 28:30.793
I know.

28:30.793 --> 28:33.295
* Rules are made to be broken

28:33.295 --> 28:34.897
Just dance with me.

28:34.897 --> 28:36.331
* Baby

28:36.331 --> 28:39.167
* I'm breakin' all my rules

28:39.167 --> 28:41.403
* For you

28:43.371 --> 28:46.474
* I know there are
certain things to wait *

28:46.474 --> 28:48.977
* Till after we're married

28:48.977 --> 28:51.413
* I know there
are certain things *

28:51.413 --> 28:54.216
* That girls aren't
supposed to do *

28:54.216 --> 28:56.151
* But I forget about the right

28:56.151 --> 28:58.353
Leah: Mommy?
* And givin' all my heart
to you *

28:58.353 --> 29:00.155
It's time
for the Graceties brunch.

29:00.155 --> 29:01.389
Are you ready?
[ Chuckles ]

29:01.389 --> 29:02.724
* To be broken

29:02.724 --> 29:05.560
Wow.
You're really just lounging?

29:05.560 --> 29:07.229
Yeah, I think we both
know better

29:07.229 --> 29:09.264
than to keep Olivia waiting.

29:09.264 --> 29:10.999
* Yeah

29:10.999 --> 29:14.169
Did you not even make it
into bed last night?

29:14.169 --> 29:15.603
* To be opened, baby

29:15.603 --> 29:16.504
Mommy.

29:16.504 --> 29:19.274
* Door to my heart is open

29:19.274 --> 29:22.878
* For you

29:22.878 --> 29:24.346
Mommy? [ Gasps ]

29:24.346 --> 29:26.014
* Baby, baby, baby

29:26.014 --> 29:29.751
Mommy? Mommy?

29:29.751 --> 29:31.019
Mommy?

29:31.019 --> 29:34.222
Mommy! [ Sobs ]

29:34.222 --> 29:37.025
* Sugar, sugar, sugar

29:37.025 --> 29:41.029
Mommy, wake up!

29:41.029 --> 29:43.198
Oh, my God!

29:43.198 --> 29:45.433
* Oh, yeah

29:45.433 --> 29:49.237
* Rules are made to be broken

29:49.237 --> 29:50.772
* Baby

29:50.772 --> 29:53.541
* I'm breakin' every rule

29:53.541 --> 29:55.243
[ Gasps ]
* For you

29:55.243 --> 29:56.744
* Yeah

29:56.744 --> 29:58.947
* Doors are made...

30:02.985 --> 30:08.924
**

30:08.924 --> 30:10.959
I wish I could go
to the funeral with you.

30:10.959 --> 30:13.561
But I have to help set up
the reception with my grandma.

30:13.561 --> 30:14.796
Quincy: Yeah, I know.

30:14.796 --> 30:17.099
Thank you for being so sweet
about this.

30:17.099 --> 30:18.300
Of course.

30:18.300 --> 30:19.601
Whatever you need,

30:19.601 --> 30:21.436
I'm here for you.

30:21.436 --> 30:23.906
[ Clears throat ]
Um...Sloane,

30:23.906 --> 30:25.473
can I get a second
with my brother, please?

30:25.473 --> 30:29.011
Sloane, you don't have
to go anywhere.

30:29.011 --> 30:31.346
**

30:31.346 --> 30:33.481
Q, it's our grandmother's
funeral.

30:33.481 --> 30:36.851
**

30:36.851 --> 30:40.288
The car's outside.
I-I brought your jacket.

30:40.288 --> 30:41.924
I got it.

30:41.924 --> 30:49.965
**

30:49.965 --> 30:58.106
**

30:58.106 --> 30:59.774
I'm proud of you.

30:59.774 --> 31:02.477
Standing up
for yourself.

31:02.477 --> 31:04.879
For us.

31:04.879 --> 31:06.481
I'll see you after,
okay?

31:06.481 --> 31:11.987
**

31:11.987 --> 31:17.225
**

31:17.225 --> 31:18.660
Darius: Hey, Trish.

31:18.660 --> 31:20.362
Thanks for meeting me
on such short notice.

31:20.362 --> 31:22.297
Hey, of course.

31:22.297 --> 31:23.498
What's so important?

31:23.498 --> 31:24.499
[ Sighs ]

31:24.499 --> 31:26.168
Why are you so nervous?

31:26.168 --> 31:27.369
I'm just a little shook.

31:27.369 --> 31:29.137
Coming back here

31:29.137 --> 31:31.373
makes me think about
all the bad things I've done.

31:31.373 --> 31:33.508
Things I blocked out
for decades.

31:33.508 --> 31:35.810
But I swear, Piggy.
I've changed.

31:35.810 --> 31:37.179
I'm a deacon
at my church now.

31:37.179 --> 31:39.681
I volunteer four times a week
down at the shelter,

31:39.681 --> 31:43.151
and I am not taking
this second chance for granted.

31:43.151 --> 31:45.387
I see you.

31:45.387 --> 31:47.055
And I believe you.

31:47.055 --> 31:50.492
Teddy Franklin
gave me another life.

31:50.492 --> 31:52.860
Thing is,
he never let me forget about it.

31:52.860 --> 31:55.030
Through the years,
my phone would ring,

31:55.030 --> 31:57.932
and it would be him
wanting a favor.

31:57.932 --> 32:01.036
To say no would risk
losing everything.

32:01.036 --> 32:02.904
So...

32:05.573 --> 32:08.510
Careful. Careful.

32:15.450 --> 32:17.685
What are you trying
to pull me into?

32:17.685 --> 32:20.555
Teddy showed up on my doorstep
one night, back in '84.

32:20.555 --> 32:21.923
He was about to join

32:21.923 --> 32:24.859
some fancy rich people club
up on the Bluffs,

32:24.859 --> 32:26.394
and so he was dressed
to the nines,

32:26.394 --> 32:27.862
you know, formal wear.

32:27.862 --> 32:30.565
His wife, too.
She was a hot mess.

32:30.565 --> 32:32.134
Looked like she had
seen a ghost.

32:32.134 --> 32:34.569
She kept mumbling something
about Eve.

32:34.569 --> 32:35.970
And before
I could say anything,

32:35.970 --> 32:37.905
Teddy shoves this gun at me
and says, "Get rid of it."

32:37.905 --> 32:40.242
Then he was gone.

32:40.242 --> 32:42.377
And I don't know why I held
onto the gun so long.

32:42.377 --> 32:45.880
I guess I thought it might serve
as some sort of leverage.

32:45.880 --> 32:47.749
But I never heard
from Teddy again.

32:47.749 --> 32:49.784
Till the other day,
which brought me to you.

32:49.784 --> 32:52.320
What do you expect me to do
with this thing?

32:52.320 --> 32:53.655
I'm not sure,

32:53.655 --> 32:55.423
but it might help 'cause,
from what I hear,

32:55.423 --> 32:57.259
he's got something
on your niece.

32:57.259 --> 32:59.594
Then I was thinking,
you couldn't fight him before,

32:59.594 --> 33:01.429
but now you can.

33:01.429 --> 33:03.498
Besides, I owe you.

33:03.498 --> 33:04.632
Look, I got to go.

33:04.632 --> 33:06.234
I got to say,
you look as beautiful

33:06.234 --> 33:08.770
as the day we first met.

33:08.770 --> 33:12.107
And I still dream
about that magnificent ass.

33:12.107 --> 33:14.109
[ Chuckles ]

33:14.109 --> 33:17.011
There's the old Darius.

33:17.011 --> 33:19.314
You take good care of yourself,
okay?

33:19.314 --> 33:20.315
You too.

33:20.315 --> 33:28.356
**

33:28.356 --> 33:29.957
Nikki:
You're not ready?

33:30.958 --> 33:32.460
Mom,
at the end of the day,

33:32.460 --> 33:33.861
Leah's still
your sister.

33:33.861 --> 33:35.363
In blood, not bond.

33:35.363 --> 33:36.464
That's not true.

33:36.464 --> 33:37.965
I see you both.

33:37.965 --> 33:39.201
She may have
broke your heart,

33:39.201 --> 33:42.337
but maybe you broke hers
a little, too.

33:42.337 --> 33:43.805
Remember
Mama Eve's funeral

33:43.805 --> 33:46.308
and that mailman she always used
to fight with came?

33:46.308 --> 33:47.809
[ Both chuckle ]
Those two
hated each other.

33:47.809 --> 33:50.044
They hated each other.

33:50.044 --> 33:52.180
But when he hugged me
and he told me,

33:52.180 --> 33:55.850
"I'm sorry for your loss,"
it meant the world to me.

33:55.850 --> 33:58.953
Now, good or bad...

33:58.953 --> 34:01.289
she's still our family.

34:01.289 --> 34:08.396
**

34:08.396 --> 34:15.837
**

34:18.573 --> 34:21.676
[ Sighs deeply ]

34:33.888 --> 34:36.023
Rose: My darling, Leah.

34:36.023 --> 34:38.393
I feel like my time has come.

34:38.393 --> 34:40.928
Soon I will move to His house.

34:40.928 --> 34:42.597
That's why I came home.

34:42.597 --> 34:46.067
So I could hold your face
and kiss it one last time.

34:46.067 --> 34:49.271
These last hours spent together
have been my happiest.

34:49.271 --> 34:51.406
You should never look back
at our relationship

34:51.406 --> 34:53.107
with any regret.

34:53.107 --> 34:55.710
Any strife between me
and your father

34:55.710 --> 34:57.512
had nothing to do with you.

34:57.512 --> 35:00.882
My life has been filled
with many blessings.

35:00.882 --> 35:02.384
But the one I hold
most precious

35:02.384 --> 35:05.287
is the wonderful gift
your father gave me,

35:05.287 --> 35:06.854
and that's you, Leah.

35:06.854 --> 35:09.391
And while the Bible says you
should honor your parents --

35:09.391 --> 35:12.394
which you have done --
I leave you with this --

35:12.394 --> 35:15.430
do not live your life
for your father.

35:15.430 --> 35:17.965
You must get out
from under his shadow.

35:17.965 --> 35:20.868
If you don't,
you will whither away.

35:20.868 --> 35:23.271
And that's one thing
about your daddy --

35:23.271 --> 35:26.408
he needs all of the sun.

35:26.408 --> 35:34.081
**

35:34.081 --> 35:41.589
**

35:41.589 --> 35:43.157
I'm ready.

35:43.157 --> 35:47.962
**

35:47.962 --> 35:50.064
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

35:50.064 --> 35:52.600
Oh, hold on.

35:52.600 --> 35:55.503
I'll be right
behind you.

35:55.503 --> 35:57.138
Okay.

36:01.075 --> 36:03.945
Brooks.
I hope this is important.

36:03.945 --> 36:05.780
Brooks: I spoke
with several ladies

36:05.780 --> 36:07.114
who were staying
at the Beach Club

36:07.114 --> 36:09.851
a week before
Jack Harmon died.

36:09.851 --> 36:11.152
Now, they remember
seeing him

36:11.152 --> 36:13.621
slip a woman a key
to his bungalow.

36:13.621 --> 36:15.757
These ladies all swear

36:15.757 --> 36:18.092
that woman was
your daughter --

36:18.092 --> 36:20.962
Leah Dupont.

36:20.962 --> 36:23.531
Well, it was smart
of you to call.

36:23.531 --> 36:26.200
Obviously,
keep this between us.

36:26.200 --> 36:32.106
**

36:35.810 --> 36:40.615
**

36:40.615 --> 36:43.351
Minister: We're here today
to mourn the passing

36:43.351 --> 36:45.186
of Sister Rose Franklin,

36:45.186 --> 36:47.289
a wife...

36:47.289 --> 36:48.856
a mother...

36:48.856 --> 36:51.626
a grandmother...

36:51.626 --> 36:53.027
a dear friend.

36:53.027 --> 36:54.629
But I am here today
to remind you

36:54.629 --> 36:56.163
that death is not the end.

36:56.163 --> 36:59.334
See, Sister Rose now
has eternal life.

36:59.334 --> 37:02.637
Like Jesus said,
"I am the light of the world:

37:02.637 --> 37:05.873
he that followeth me
shall not walk in darkness,

37:05.873 --> 37:07.875
but shall have
the light of life."

37:07.875 --> 37:10.645
Forever and ever, amen.

37:10.645 --> 37:11.846
Together: Amen.

37:11.846 --> 37:18.686
**

37:18.686 --> 37:25.560
**

37:25.560 --> 37:27.362
Rose.

37:27.362 --> 37:30.998
I prayed I would not live
to see this day.

37:30.998 --> 37:32.600
I tried to do right by you,

37:32.600 --> 37:36.904
but I'd be lying if I claimed
to have executed that plan.

37:36.904 --> 37:40.408
People who are loved
never really die.

37:40.408 --> 37:44.879
They live on through those
they have touched.

37:46.280 --> 37:50.752
Quincy, you have
Rose's courage.

37:50.752 --> 37:52.787
Lauren...

37:52.787 --> 37:54.422
her fire.

37:54.422 --> 37:57.692
**

37:57.692 --> 37:59.561
Leah...

37:59.561 --> 38:02.296
her unyielding strength.

38:02.296 --> 38:06.434
I know that this shared grief
will bring us even closer.

38:06.434 --> 38:13.608
Rose, as I look at our
beautiful family every day,

38:13.608 --> 38:16.544
I know that what we built
together was not in vain.

38:16.544 --> 38:19.414
So rest assured, Rose...

38:19.414 --> 38:20.648
**

38:20.648 --> 38:23.451
...that your family
will miss you dearly.

38:23.451 --> 38:30.425
**

38:30.425 --> 38:37.131
**

38:37.131 --> 38:39.000
Olivia:
As most of you know,

38:39.000 --> 38:42.970
Rose Franklin
was my dearest friend.

38:45.473 --> 38:48.242
And today...

38:48.242 --> 38:51.145
our fellow Graceties

38:51.145 --> 38:54.616
are going to join me
in singing a chorus

38:54.616 --> 38:58.653
from her sisters
to wave her up to Heaven.

38:58.653 --> 39:00.655
[ Piano plays ]

39:00.655 --> 39:09.096
* Precious Lord

39:09.096 --> 39:13.668
* Take

39:13.668 --> 39:18.139
* My hand

39:19.841 --> 39:23.611
* Lead

39:23.611 --> 39:27.014
* Lead me on

39:27.014 --> 39:33.287
* And let me stand

39:33.287 --> 39:37.725
* Through the storm

39:37.725 --> 39:41.395
* Through the storm

39:41.395 --> 39:46.534
* All through the night

39:46.534 --> 39:48.202
* Mm

39:48.202 --> 39:49.871
* Ohh, ohh, ohh

39:49.871 --> 39:54.041
* Take my hand

39:54.041 --> 39:56.911
**

39:56.911 --> 39:59.413
[ Chuckles ]

39:59.413 --> 40:03.217
I know you thought
you were weak.

40:03.217 --> 40:07.188
But you were the strongest woman
I've ever known.

40:07.188 --> 40:10.658
I am so proud
to be your daughter.

40:10.658 --> 40:13.260
[ Sniffles ]

40:14.529 --> 40:18.232
You deserved so much more
than you got from this life.

40:20.702 --> 40:22.604
I will honor you...

40:22.604 --> 40:24.706
for the rest of my days.

40:24.706 --> 40:32.079
**

40:32.079 --> 40:39.754
**

40:39.754 --> 40:40.955
[ Sobs ]

40:40.955 --> 40:44.592
* Ohh, ohh, ohh

40:44.592 --> 40:49.731
* Take my hand

40:49.731 --> 40:58.606
* Precious Lord

40:58.606 --> 41:03.277
* Lead me home

41:03.277 --> 41:06.113
* Mm, mm, mmm

41:10.451 --> 41:13.555
There's a certain cry
at funerals.

41:13.555 --> 41:16.490
It's a wail
that comes from the gut.

41:19.126 --> 41:22.764
With everything that's happened
between me and Leah,

41:22.764 --> 41:26.167
I wouldn't wish that pain
on anybody.

41:33.641 --> 41:36.410
Whose gun is that?

41:36.410 --> 41:39.146
According to Darius,
it's Teddy's.

41:39.146 --> 41:40.748
He said Teddy gave it
to him to hide

41:40.748 --> 41:42.584
the night that
your mother was arrested.

41:42.584 --> 41:44.151
What else did
Darius say?

41:44.151 --> 41:46.654
I don't know any more, baby,
and neither does Darius.

41:46.654 --> 41:49.123
But the only reason
that someone hides a gun

41:49.123 --> 41:52.627
is if it's used
in a crime.

41:52.627 --> 41:54.028
Oh.

41:54.028 --> 41:55.597
Well, then we are
gonna figure out

41:55.597 --> 41:58.499
exactly what
my father did.

41:58.499 --> 42:02.169
Oh, get ready, Teddy,
'cause I'm coming for you.

42:02.169 --> 42:03.838
We're coming.

42:03.838 --> 42:05.206
For Eve.

42:05.206 --> 42:07.174
For Eve.

42:07.174 --> 42:14.181
**

42:17.985 --> 42:27.729
**

42:27.795 --> 42:37.571
**

42:37.571 --> 42:46.580
**

42:54.355 --> 42:57.091
Don't miss the new series,
our kind of people.

42:57.191 --> 42:58.926
Tuesdays on Fox.
